15/12/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Southeast European Police Chiefs Association (SEPCA) opened its two-day conference in Sarajevo on Thursday (December 14th).
Senior police officials from Macedonia, Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bulgaria, Montenegro, Croatia, Romania and Serbia are on hand, discussing the possible introduction of a global police communication system I-24/7 at border posts in the region.
The I-24/7 system would connect various law enforcement officials and help border police to search and crosscheck data in a matter of seconds.
(RTRS, PBS, Makfax - 14/12/06)
